<subSubSection id="4984EE782198F2850A7B7C1CD92E3940" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" type="notes">
<paragraph id="94890330B075530AA59CFC4F0719BCAA" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CCEB15A694E5B39108065996BEEC7769" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176">
This species was commonly encountered in the sandy washes immediately surrounding MDRS (Fig. 31). Widely variable across its range, 
<bibRefCitation id="0061961C90682913B7B2D27E6266321F" author="Welsh, S. L." journalOrPublisher="Print Services, Brigham Young University, Provo" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" title="A Utah Flora" year="1993">Welsh et al. (1993)</bibRefCitation>
report nine named varieties in Utah, and 
<bibRefCitation id="14DB1606D486A91A8E409FADF852984F" author="Harris, JG" journalOrPublisher="Great Basin Naturalist" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" pagination="79 - 87" title="A vascular flora of the San Rafael Swell, Utah" volume="43" year="1983">Harris (1983)</bibRefCitation>
reports 
<taxonomicName id="21B7F405780465D0E581D3CD10B7DCEC" authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Chironomidae" genus="L." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="L. montanum var. jonesii" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="variety" species="montanum" variety="jonesii">L. montanum var. jonesii</taxonomicName>
(Rydb.) C.L. Hitch. from the nearby San Rafael Swell. 
<bibRefCitation id="8C204CE47806AC9404477279E0554052" author="Al-Shebaz, IA" editor="Flora of North America Editorial Committee, eds." journalOrPublisher="New York and Oxford" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" title="Flora of North America North of Mexico" year="2010">Al-Shebaz and Gaskin (2010)</bibRefCitation>
subsume these varieties into 
<taxonomicName id="FC873D14AFE07F483C4B94E0C77A6E93" authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Chironomidae" genus="L." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="L. montanum" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="species" species="montanum">L. montanum</taxonomicName>
sensu lato pending a thorough study of infraspecific delimitation; we follow their treatment here.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C0A9B870229BA04774586044178C7F0E" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176">Supplemental Files: CAN 607467 (Suppl. material 41), CAN 607471 (Suppl. material 42).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
